        "start": 0.0,
        "end": 21.161
      },
      {
        "segment": "I am Ra.",
        "start_offset": 141,
        "end_offset": 149,
        "start": 21.481,
        "end": 23.961
      },
      {
        "segment": "The distortion referred to above; that is, the complex of juvenile rheumatoid arthritis and lupus erythematosus acts in such a way as to cause various portions of the body complex to become distorted in the way in which the instrument's pedal appendages are now distorted.",
        "start_offset": 150,
        "end_offset": 422,
        "start": 23.981,
        "end": 104.063
      },
      {
        "segment": "We may suggest care in resumption of the exercise but determination as well.",
        "start_offset": 423,
        "end_offset": 499,
        "start": 107.723,
        "end": 130.664
      },
      {
        "segment": "The alternation of footwear shall prove efficacious.",
        "start_offset": 500,
        "end_offset": 552,
        "start": 133.144,
        "end": 146.384
      },
      {
        "segment": "The undergarment for the feet which you call the anklet should be of a softer and finer material than is now being used and should, if possible, conform more to the outline of those appendages upon which it is placed.",
        "start_offset": 553,
        "end_offset": 770,
        "start": 149.704,
        "end": 210.126
      },
      {
        "segment": "This should provide a more efficient aid to the cushioning of these appendages.",
        "start_offset": 771,
        "end_offset": 850,
        "start": 211.606,
        "end": 233.027
      },
      {
        "segment": "We may further suggest that the same immersion in the waters which is helpful to the general distortion is, in general, helpful to this specific distortion as well.",
        "start_offset": 851,
        "end_offset": 1015,
        "start": 235.887,
        "end": 276.648
      },
      {
        "segment": "However, the injury which has been sustained in the metatarsal region of the right pedal appendage should further be treated for some period of your space/time by the prudent application of the ice to the arch of the right foot for brief periods followed always by immersion in the warm water.",
        "start_offset": 1016,
        "end_offset": 1309,
        "start": 278.148,
        "end": 351.01
      }
